<topic id="author-teip5-doc-type">
  <title>TEI P5 Framework (Document Type)</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Predefined frameworks<indexterm>TEI P5</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>TEI P5 document type</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/tei-intro"/>
    <section id="file_definition">
      <title>File Definition</title>
      <p>A file is considered to be a TEI P5 document when one of the following conditions are
        true:</p>
      <ul id="ul_ihz_3jf_fr">
        <li>The document namespace is <i>http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0</i>.</li>
        <li>The public id of the document is <i>-//TEI P5</i>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="document_templates">
      <title>Default Document Templates</title>
      <p>There are a variety of default <i>TEI P5</i> templates available when creating <xref
          href="new-dialog-sa.dita#new-dialog-sa" product="author developer editor">new documents
          from templates</xref><xref href="creating-from-templates.dita#creating-from-templates"
          product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">new documents from
        templates</xref>, including <uicontrol>Bare</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Lite</uicontrol>,
          <uicontrol>Math</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Speech</uicontrol>, and more.</p>
      <p>The default templates for TEI P5 documents are located in the <filepath><term
            conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>/frameworks/tei/templates/TEI
          P5</filepath> folder.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="default_schema">
      <title>Default Schema</title>
      <p>The default schema that is used if one is not detected in the TEI P5 document is
          <filepath>tei_all.rng</filepath> and it is stored in <filepath><term
            conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
          />/frameworks/tei/xml/tei/custom/schema/relaxng/</filepath>.</p>
    </section>
    <section product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse" id="default_css">
      <title>Default CSS</title>
      <p>The default CSS files used for rendering TEI content in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode
        are stored in <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
          />/frameworks/tei/xml/tei/css/</filepath>.</p>
      <p>By default, these default CSS files are merged with any that are specified in the document.
        For more information, see <xref
          href="selecting-combining-multiple-css-styles.dita#selecting-combining-multiple-css-styles"
        />.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="default_xml_catalogs">
      <title>Default XML Catalogs</title>
      <p>The default catalogs for the TEI P5 document type are as follows:</p>
      <ul id="ul_phz_rpg_wq">
        <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
            />/frameworks/tei/xml/tei/schema/dtd/catalog.xml</filepath></li>
        <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
            />/frameworks/tei/xml/tei/custom/schema/dtd/catalog.xml</filepath></li>
        <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
            />/frameworks/tei/xml/tei/stylesheet/catalog.xml</filepath></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
